== Roasted Broccoli ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a medium #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

== Bacon ==

Arrange @bacon{4%oz} in a single layer on a separate #baking sheet{}. Roast on middle rack until crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Toasted Everything-Bagel Breadcrumbs ==

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @everything bagel seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a small #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Cream Cheese Sauce ==

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain, then return pasta to pot.

While pasta cooks, in #pan used for panko, whisk together @cream sauce base{4%oz} and @water{1%cup} (2 cups for 4 servings) over medium heat. Bring to a simmer.

Add @cream cheese{6%tbsp}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, and @garlic powder{1%tsp}. Cook, whisking, until cream cheese is fully incorporated and sauce is smooth, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Whisk in three-quarters of the @cheddar cheese{2%cups} and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted and smooth. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

== Mac 'n' Cheese ==

Transfer cheese sauce to pot with drained cavatappi; stir to combine.

Coat an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} (9-by-13-inch baking dish for 4 servings) with @nonstick cooking spray{}. Transfer mac 'n' cheese to prepared #baking dish{}.

Top with remaining cheddar and bake on middle rack until browned, ~{12-15%minutes}. Let rest ~{5%minutes} before serving.

== Pickled Jalapeños and Sides ==

While mac 'n' cheese bakes, halve @jalapeño{1} lengthwise, removing ribs and seeds for less heat; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Dice @tomato{1} into 1/2-inch pieces.

In a second small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine jalapeño, @white wine vinegar{1%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. (Save remaining vinegar for another use.) Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

> For 4 servings, use 2 tsp vinegar, 1/2 tsp sugar, and a big pinch of salt.

== To Serve ==

Serve broccoli, mac 'n' cheese, toasted panko, tomato, and pickled jalapeño family style and let everyone build their own plate.

Serve chopped bacon with mac 'n' cheese bar.

> Order bacon for smoky crispness and/or hot honey for sweet spice.